§ 1⁷. If a depositary fraudulently enabled a depositum to be stolen, he was liable to actio depositi, and could not sue the thies himself, ‘ non enim debet ex dolo suo furti quaerere actionem' Dig. 47. 2. 14. 3 and 4. He was also liable if he had undertaken the custodia, note on Bk. iii. 14. 3 supr.‚ and then apparently could bring the penal action, Dig. 47. 2. 14. 16 ; 47. 8. 2. 23 and 24.
